25#include <sys/cdefs.h>
26__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_bios_shadowramin.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:33 riastradh Exp $");
27
28#include "priv.h"
29
30struct priv {
31 struct nvkm_bios *bios;
32 u32 bar0;
33};
34
35static u32
36pramin_read(void *data, u32 offset, u32 length, struct nvkm_bios *bios)
37{
38 struct nvkm_device *device = bios->subdev.device;
39 u32 i;
40 if (offset + length <= 0x00100000) {
41 for (i = offset; i < offset + length; i += 4)
42 *(u32 *)&bios->data[i] = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x700000 + i);
43 return length;
44 }
45 return 0;
46}
47
48static void
49pramin_fini(void *data)
50{
51 struct priv *priv = data;
52 if (priv) {
53 struct nvkm_device *device = priv->bios->subdev.device;
54 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001700, priv->bar0);
55 kfree(priv);
56 }
57}
58
59static void *
60pramin_init(struct nvkm_bios *bios, const char *name)
61{
62 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &bios->subdev;
63 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
64 struct priv *priv = NULL;
65 u64 addr = 0;
66
67 /* PRAMIN always potentially available prior to nv50 */
68 if (device->card_type < NV_50)
69 return NULL;
70
71 /* we can't get the bios image pointer without PDISP */
72 if (device->card_type >= GM100)
73 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x021c04);
74 else
75 if (device->card_type >= NV_C0)
76 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022500);
77 if (addr & 0x00000001) {
78 nvkm_debug(subdev, "... display disabled\n");
79 return ERR_PTR(-ENODEV);
80 }
81
82 /* check that the window is enabled and in vram, particularly
83 * important as we don't want to be touching vram on an
84 * uninitialised board
85 */
86 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x619f04);
87 if (!(addr & 0x00000008)) {
88 nvkm_debug(subdev, "... not enabled\n");
89 return ERR_PTR(-ENODEV);
90 }
91 if ( (addr & 0x00000003) != 1) {
92 nvkm_debug(subdev, "... not in vram\n");
93 return ERR_PTR(-ENODEV);
94 }
95
96 /* some alternate method inherited from xf86-video-nv... */
97 addr = (addr & 0xffffff00) << 8;
98 if (!addr) {
99 addr = (u64)nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001700) << 16;
100 addr += 0xf0000;
101 }
102
103 /* modify bar0 PRAMIN window to cover the bios image */
104 if (!(priv = kmalloc(sizeof(*priv), GFP_KERNEL))) {
105 nvkm_error(subdev, "... out of memory\n");
106 return ERR_PTR(-ENOMEM);
107 }
108
109 priv->bios = bios;
110 priv->bar0 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x001700);
111 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x001700, addr >> 16);
112 return priv;
113}
114
115const struct nvbios_source
116nvbios_ramin = {
117 .name = "PRAMIN",
118 .init = pramin_init,
119 .fini = pramin_fini,
120 .read = pramin_read,
121 .rw = true,
122};
